---

##  Prerequisites

- **Node.js** (v18 or higher)
- **npm** or **yarn**
- **Google Gemini API Key** (free from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey))

---

##  Running Locally

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/discvrai-assignment.git
cd discvrai-assignment


# Navigate to backend folder
cd server

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create environment file
cp .env.example .env

# Edit .env and add your Gemini API key
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# PORT=5000

# Start the backend server
npm run dev


# Open a new terminal
cd frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start the React app
npm start


discvrai-assignment/
├── server/                 # Backend
│   ├── index.js           # Main server file
│   ├── products.js        # Product catalog (45+ items)
│   ├── .env               # Environment variables
│   └── package.json
│
└── frontend/              # Frontend
    ├── public/
    ├── src/
    │   ├── components/
    │   │   ├── AskQuery.js        # AI search component
    │   │   ├── ProductList.js     # Product grid component
    │   │   └── styles/            # CSS files
    │   │       ├── AskQuery.css
    │   │       └── ProductList.css
    │   ├── App.js
    │   ├── App.css
    │   └── index.js
    └── package.json


    # Google Gemini API Key - Get one for free at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# Server port (default: 5000)
PORT=5000




json
🌐 API Endpoints
Method	Endpoint	Description	Request Body
GET	/api/products	Get all products	-
GET	/api/test-gemini	Test Gemini connection	-
POST	/api/ask	AI product search	{ "query": "your question" }
Example API Response
POST /api/ask

json
{
  "query": "show me laptops",
  "answer": "I found some great laptops for you!",
  "products": [
    {
      "id": "P001",
      "name": "MacBook Pro 16\"",
      "category": "Electronics",
      "price": 2499.99,
